<para>
  Minimum thresholding finds a minimum in a smoothed histogram of the
  intensities in an &image;, and converts all pixels brighter than the
  miniumum to white and all pixels darker than it to black.
</para>
<para>
   The &image; is first converted from color to grayscale if
   necessary.
</para>
<para>
  <classname>MinimumThreshold</classname> is a wrapper around the
  &skimage; routine <ulink
  url="https://scikit-image.org/docs/stable/api/skimage.filters.html#skimage.filters.threshold_minimum"
  role="external"><code>skimage.filters.threshold_minimum</code></ulink>.
</para>
  

